  "text": "Recent studies demonstrate that besides hyperglycemia, recurrent hypoglycemia also affects brain functions in terms of causing cognitive dysfunction [CITATION_1] , anxiety and depression [CITATION_2] . In an earlier study we demonstrated that exposure to recurrent hypoglycemia before cerebral ischemia can increase cerebral ischemic damage in a rat model of Type 1 diabetes [CITATION_3] .",
